    "department": "Operations",
    "description": "ABOUT JUICEBOX\n\nJuicebox is on a mission to help teams win the talent war.\n\nIn the age of AI, human ingenuity is the ultimate scarce resource. Recruiting is a zero-sum game where you either compete or lose.\n\nTeams at Ramp, Notion, and leading AI labs use Juicebox to power their hiring, alongside 5,000+ customers from early-stage startups to Fortune 500 companies.\n\nWe are on the path to $100M in ARR with 20%+ monthly growth, powering thousands of searches every day and making Juicebox one of the fastest-growing AI SaaS companies in the world.\n\nJuicebox has raised over $116M in funding from lead investors including Sequoia Capital, DST Global, and NFDG. Read more about our $80M Series B https://juicebox.ai/blog/series-b here. Additional investors in Juicebox include Y Combinator, Coatue, Bond, Lux, Verified Capital, and Committed Capital.\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nWe’re hiring a Business Operations generalist to work directly with the CEO and leadership team on the highest-impact priorities across the company.\n\nThis is a true generalist role: you’ll operate as a force multiplier across go-to-market, product, and operations, owning ambiguous, project-based work that drives critical business outcomes.\n\nAs one of the first BizOps hires, you’ll have outsized ownership and visibility, directly influencing company trajectory through cross-functional initiatives.\n\n\nYOU WILL\n\n - Tackle and drive some of Juicebox’s high-priority, cross-functional projects across Sales, Product, and GTM, from problem definition through execution\n\n - Partner with the CEO and leadership team to inform strategy, set priorities, and drive key business decisions\n\n - Build internal AI tooling to make existing business processes more efficient\n\n - Develop dashboards, KPIs, and reporting to provide visibility into company performance (pipeline, growth, retention, etc.)\n\n - Identify bottlenecks and opportunities across the business, and lead initiatives to improve efficiency and outcomes\n\n - Stand up new functions, workflows, and systems from scratch as the company grows\n\n\nYOU HAVE\n\n - Have 2+ years of experience in Business Operations, Strategy, Consulting, or a similar generalist role (4+ years preferred)\n\n - Are highly structured and analytical, with strong problem-solving skills\n\n - Thrive in ambiguity and enjoy owning problems end-to-end\n\n - Have experience working cross-functionally with GTM, product, or operations teams\n\n - Are proficient with spreadsheets, analytics tools, and systems (CRM experience a plus)\n\n - Move quickly, communicate clearly, and have strong business judgment\n\n - Are based in SF or open to relocating (in-office 5 days/week)\n\n - Want to work hard (more than regular hours) for a high-impact, rewarding role\n\n\nNICE TO HAVE\n\n - Experience in B2B SaaS, recruiting tech, or AI\n\n - Experience with AI tooling / have built your own tools\n\n - Experience as an early BizOps, Strategy, or first operations hire at a startup",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
